This paper deals with the application of network coding in a wired network, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The analysis is done using game theory, which suggests the paper could also be classified under the categories of game theory (cs.GT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses resource allocation and pricing schemes, which could place it under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
